detail.title: Stride v10 Perseus Release
detail.description:
**Stride v10 Perseus Release**

This is a proposal to upgrade the chain to the v10.0.0 tag (“Perseus” Release) of the Stride codebase at block height 4,191,914 which is estimated to occur on Tuesday, June 20th 2023 at 12 UTC. Because of the uncertainty in block times, please keep track of the Stride chain for a precise estimate. 

**Upgrade Features**

This upgrade adds the following features:

- SDK 47 / IBC v7
- IBC Rate Limiting Audit Fixes
- Fund Bad Kids per Prop 205

**Getting Prepared for the Upgrade**

As always, we recommend validators use 64GB of RAM. If you are unable to have 64GB of RAM, at a minimum have a total of 64GB of swap set to prevent out of memory errors.

We _highly_ recommend upgrading with Cosmovisor. To do this, please manually build & copy the strided binary to /cosmovisor/upgrades/v10/bin/.

**Details of Upgrade Time**

The proposal targets the upgrade proposal block to be 4,191,914, anticipated to be on  Wednesday, June 20th 2023 at 12 UTC. Because blocks can occur at irregular intervals, please keep an eye on the Stride chain for a precise upgrade time.  

In case anything concerning happens at upgrade time, we will notify all validators immediately on the #validator-announcements channel on Discord and telegram.

detail.title: Stride and Carbon Alliance Proposal: stLUNA as Carbon's Alliance Asset and STRD incentives for STRD collateral
detail.description:
## Stride and Carbon Alliance Proposal: stLUNA as Carbon's Alliance Asset and STRD incentives for STRD collateral

### Summary
This proposal seeks to request 2050 STRD tokens from the STRD community pool to provide incentives for the STRD lending pool on Carbon. By doing so, we can boost the utility, buying pressure, and adoption of the STRD token, as well as raise awareness about the Carbon <> Stride Alliance.

### Description
Stride is the most popular and largest liquid staking provider on Cosmos, and Carbon had the privilege of being the first money market on Cosmos to support Stride's stTokens by whitelisting stATOM, stOSMO, stJUNO, stEVMOS, and STRD as collateral on Carbon's frontend UI, Demex.

Carbon envisions a long-term partnership with Stride, and is listing stLUNA as an Alliance asset on Carbon chain, marking Stride's first alliance asset of another chain, with more to come. 

Listing stLUNA as an Alliance asset means that stLUNA can be staked on Carbon network to receive Carbon's staking reward on top stLUNA's yield, which further increases stLUNA's yield and demand, which will grow stLUNA's TVL and ultimately provides more fees back to STRD holders.

As of this writing, there's about $100k worth of STRD collateral, and $200k worth of stAssets on Carbon's money market, Nitron. As a goodwill gesture, Carbon has proactively provided SWTH token incentives to STRD lending pool to bootstrap liquidity. This forum post is to discuss providing STRD incentives from the Stride community pool to the STRD lending pool on Carbon to further increase the utility, buying pressure, and adoption of the STRD token, as well as a way to help raise more awareness of Stride and Carbon Alliance.

More context and benefits to Stride can be found at the Commonwealth forum here: https://commonwealth.im/stride/discussion/11529-stride-and-carbon-alliance-proposal-stluna-as-carbons-alliance-asset-and-strd-incentives-for-strd-collateral 

#### Where do the funds go?
This proposal, if accepted, will spend 2050 STRD tokens from the community pool, which is worth about $2,500 and 10% of the pool at this point in time, to the dev team address at stride1azgv7znw27cxfs66hj0ak0yv5a4xvtej27zf5m on Stride network in order to fund the external incentive module on Nitron according to the parameters of this proposal. 

### The Proposer

- CJ @fishmarketacad, BizDev at Carbon Network

detail.title: Join ATOM Economic Zone and adopt ICS
detail.description:
**Summary**

This is a signaling proposal for the Stride blockchain to join the ATOM Economic Zone and adopt interchain security (ICS) from Cosmos Hub.

If STRD stakers approve this signaling proposal, it would indicate their willingness to join the AEZ and adopt ICS according to the given terms. In this case, the next step would be to make an onchain signaling proposal for Cosmos Hub, which would go live on April 27th. This proposal will only be implemented if both STRD stakers and ATOM stakers approve.

Under this proposal, Stride would share its various revenues with Cosmos Hub as follows:

- 15% of liquid staking rewards
- 15% of STRD inflationary staking rewards
- 15% of maximal extractible value (MEV) revenue
- 15% of transaction fees

In return, Cosmos Hub would share its economic security with Stride. Also, since Stride would be part of the ATOM Economic Zone, Cosmos Hub would share 450,000 ATOM, to be provided to an stATOM/ATOM liquidity pool on Astroport’s Neutron deployment. These funds would be used to facilitate trading between stATOM and ATOM, would not be spent in any way, would remain the property of Cosmos Hub, and would always remain under the control of Cosmos Hub.

This proposal also signals support for a special staking reward reduction of 50% on inflationary STRD staking rewards, to coincide with Stride’s potential adoption of ICS.

**Governance votes**

The following items describe the voting options and their significance for this proposal:

- **YES** - You agree with all the terms of this proposal, the main terms being: 1) Cosmos Hub shares its economic security with Stride, 2) Cosmos Hub shares 450K of ATOM liquidity, 3) Stride shares 15% of all its revenues with Cosmos Hub, and 4) inflationary STRD staking rewards are decreased by 50% with a special halvening when Stride adopts ICS
- **NO** - You do not agree with all the terms of this proposal. You may agree with some terms and disagree with others. But if you do not agree with all terms, vote NO
- **NO WITH VETO** - You 1) consider this proposal to be spam, 2) believe it infringes on minority interests. If the number of NoWithVeto votes is greater than a third of total votes, the proposal is rejected and the deposits are burned
- **ABSTAIN** - You wish to contribute to quorum but you formally decline to vote either for or against the proposal

See the full proposal here:
https://commonwealth.im/stride/discussion/11131-stride-to-join-atom-economic-zone-and-adopt-ics

detail.title: Enable Autopilot
detail.description:
This is a parameter change proposal to enable Autopilot (1-click liquid staking) on Stride to improve the liquid staking UX.

**Autopilot Description**

Autopilot is an IBC middleware that will allow users to liquid stake their tokens in one transaction, improving the Stride UX. In particular, it will allow a user to send an IBC transfer with a memo signaling the tokens should be liquid staked, and have the liquid staked version end up in their wallet. More details can be found in the x/autopilot README: https://github.com/Stride-Labs/stride/blob/main/x/autopilot/README.md

The Autopilot code has already been added to the Stride codebase, this proposal would NOT initiate a software upgrade. Rather, this proposal would activate the described feature.

**Vote Options**

Vote **YES** to turn on Autopilot for liquid staking.
Vote **NO** to keep Autopilot off.
Vote **NO WITH VETO** to indicate this proposal either (1) is deemed to be spam, i.e. irrelevant to Stride, (2) disproportionately infringes on minority interests, or (3) violates or encourages violation of the rules of engagement as currently set out by Stride. If the number of 'NoWithVeto' votes is greater than a third of total votes, the proposal is rejected and the deposits are burned.
Vote **ABSTAIN** if you wish to contribute to the quorum but formally decline to vote either for or against the proposal.

detail.title: Incentive Diversification
detail.description:
This is a signaling proposal to diversify the Incentive Program by swapping 3M STRD for 1.5M USDC. The USDC will be fully used for the incentive program, to encourage liquidity and adoption of Stride’s stTokens.

More context for this discussion can be found on Commonwealth here: https://commonwealth.im/stride/discussion/9991-incentive-diversification

3M STRD should be sent from the incentive program (stride1tlxk4as9sgpqkh42cfaxqja0mdj6qculqshy0gg3glazmrnx3y8s8gsvqk) to the Stride Foundation (stride1yz3mp7c2m739nftfrv5r3h6j64aqp95f3degpf) during the next software upgrade. Immediately after, Multicoin and North Island Ventures will send 750,000 USDC to the Stride Foundation each, for a total of 1,500,000 USDC. The Foundation will then deposit 1.5M STRD each into 2 Vesting Accounts, where tokens start vesting after 12 months, and vest linearly until 36 months. The USDC will be deployed as incentives from the Stride Foundation. No funds will be used for any other purpose.

Vote YES on this proposal to signal support for the incentive swap.

Vote NO on this proposal if you do NOT want to support the incentive swap.

detail.title: Parameter Change: Increase Deposit for Proposals to 2000 STRD
detail.description:
### Details 
 
  The current deposit for a governance proposal is 10 STRD, worth approximately $3 in the current market. 2000 STRD has a current market value of approximately $600 and represents a more significant penalty to discourage spam proposals such as [Proposal 14](https://www.mintscan.io/stride/proposals/14). Deposits may be filled by more than one party using the command line or wallet interfaces, such as [Commonwealth](https://commonwealth.im/stride/discussions) and [ping.pub](https://ping.pub/stride/gov), to ensure that the community is not priced out of governance. Governance participants should regularly re-evaluate this parameter against STRD price to ensure it is an appropriate spam deterrent whilst also being accessible. 
 
  ### Voting 
 
  * Voting YES for this proposal will adjust the deposit required for a proposal to enter the voting period to 2000 STRD. 
 * Voting NO for this proposal will keep the deposit required for a proposal to enter the voting period at 10 STRD. 
 
  **[Proposal 19](https://www.mintscan.io/stride/proposals/19) has wrong subkeys, so it won't affect on blockchain parameters.** 
 
  #### Authors 

  * Alphabet validator 
 * Pro-Nodes75 validator

This will lower the relevant threshold and allow us to rebalance to our target.

detail.title: Setting Stride's Roadmap for 2023
detail.description:
This proposal is intended to signal a list of key community-requested features to include in the roadmap for the Stride Ecosystem in 2023. These features were pulled from community feedback in Stride’s social channels, as well as from conversations with community members and ecosystem contributors.

This proposal is not intended to constrain Stride contributors by requiring that they focus only on these roadmap items or by requiring that all of these features be launched in 2023. This list is meant only to help guide Stride contributors to focus on features that STRD tokenholders wish to see implemented.
The list of proposed roadmap items can be found below.

**Security**

- -Bug Bounty

- -Ongoing Audits

- -IBC rate limiting

**Liquid Governance**

- -Liquid Governance V1: Vote from the Stride blockchain

- -Liquid Governance V2: Vote using stAssets held in Osmosis Liquidity Pools

- -Liquid Governance V3: Vote from anywhere in Cosmos

**User Experience**

- -Stride frontend redesign

- -1-click liquid staking (ibc-transfer and liquid stake in a single transaction)

- -The liquid staking module

**Data**

- -DeFi integrations dashboard

- -Liquid staking dashboard (TVL, redemption rate, rewards paid, validator set)

- -Incentives calendar

**Research**

- -Instant Redemptions (Redeem stAssets without waiting for the unstaking period)

- -Inter Chain Validator Indices

- -Protocol-Controlled stToken Pool Arbitrage

- -Interchain Validator Data Wiki

- -Cosmos stTokens bridged to Ethereum via Axelar

- -Cosmos stTokens bridged to NEAR and Polkadot via Composable Finance

- -Staking derivatives of non-Cosmos PoS Chains

- -Relayer fee market middleware

Vote YES on this proposal to ratify the foregoing roadmap and signal community consent to Stride contributors to action these roadmap items for 2023.

Vote NO on this proposal if you disagree with the outcome of this proposal or with this list of roadmap items.

detail.title: Re-Allocate the Stride Protocol Commission Fee
detail.description:
### Re-Allocate the Stride Protocol Commission Fee
Stride Protocol is in the midst of a period of explosive growth, having onboarded four liquid staking derivatives (stATOM, stJUNO, stSTARS, stOSMO) in the two months since launch of the protocol, with plans to onboard many more assets in the coming months. To bootstrap liquidity and usage of these stAssets, Stride has heavily incentivized liquidity on Osmosis with the native STRD token.

While this strategy is proving widely successful thus far (stAsset liquidity will soon surpass the 0 million TVL threshold), it has also had the effect of placing additional selling pressure on the STRD token and rapidly inflating circulating supply. STRD’s current staked/circulating supply ratio is just over 10%. For security purposes, this ratio should be increased. Ideally, a protocol’s tokenomic model should have the following goals:
 * Bring value to STRD stakers in exchange for locking up tokens as a service to the protocol.
 * Contribute to the success of the protocol by incentivizing and empowering the community.
 * Increase chain security by raising the bonded ratio of tokens.

This proposal aims to accomplish all of these goals by diverting the Stride protocol host chain staking reward commission to STRD stakers.

### Background:
Stride collects 10% of all staking rewards from host chain assets staked through the protocol. Currently, these rewards are accumulating in an on-chain module account. According to Stride’s tokenomics paper, the community will decide the disposition of these rewards. 

### Proposal:
This proposal aims to accomplish the following objectives:
 * Signal to Stride development contributors that the Stride community desires an in-protocol solution to allocate the Stride host-chain staking reward commission fee according to governance-mutable parameters. 
 * Allocate the Stride host chain staking reward commission fee to STRD stakers according to stake weight.

#### Building a Solution to Allocate the Stride Commission Fee
The on-chain parameters necessary to implement this proposal in its entirety do not exist yet, so the proposal will need to be carried out via a subsequent software upgrade. The following is a set of guidelines meant to aid the Stride’s development contributors in building the necessary module flow.

First, the Stride host chain staking reward commission should be capable of being reallocated in a manner that is fully controllable by governance via parameter change proposals. The commission fee should also be capable of being streamed to multiple destination accounts at once (i.e. 10% to account A, 40% to account B, 50% to account C).
So long as the provisions of this proposal are met, the manner of distribution should be left to the discretion of Stride development contributors, who are better suited to understand the development and implementation challenges that go along with distribution.

Swapping the collected rewards to STRD can be accomplished by executing an interchain accounts call from the module responsible for distribution (or some intermediary module) in a manner that:
 * Performs an IBC transfer of the reward asset from Stride > the asset’s native chain > Osmosis; 
 * Swaps the reward asset to STRD on Osmosis;
 * Performs an IBC transfer of the STRD from Osmosis back to Stride chain to be distributed

This can be done in real time as rewards are collected or, if more technically feasible / desirable, at one or more set intervals (epochs) each day.
Second, the rewards that have already been collected should be distributed according to the allocations set forth in this proposal immediately upon implementation of this proposal (or at the first possible epoch following implementation of this proposal if an epoch model is utilized).

#### Allocate the Stride Host Chain Reward Commission to STRD Delegators
To compensate STRD holders for staking their tokens and increase the security of the chain, this proposal seeks to allocate the Stride host chain staking reward commission fee directly to STRD delegators. Using the USD equivalent of the current projected annual rewards of 50,000 and the current bonded ratio, this would provide STRD delegators with an APR of approximately (4.2)%.

### Execution of this Proposal:
Should this proposal pass, Stride development contributors should begin developing the module flow according to the guidelines set forth herein. Once completed and tested, a software upgrade proposal will be put on chain explaining the module flow and the initial commission fee allocations outlined in this proposal.

**The full text of this proposal can be found here:**
https://commonwealth.im/stride/discussion/7652-signaling-proposal-reallocate-the-stride-protocol-commission-fee

content.title: Re-Allocate the Stride Protocol Commission Fee
content.description:
### Re-Allocate the Stride Protocol Commission Fee
Stride Protocol is in the midst of a period of explosive growth, having onboarded four liquid staking derivatives (stATOM, stJUNO, stSTARS, stOSMO) in the two months since launch of the protocol, with plans to onboard many more assets in the coming months. To bootstrap liquidity and usage of these stAssets, Stride has heavily incentivized liquidity on Osmosis with the native STRD token.

While this strategy is proving widely successful thus far (stAsset liquidity will soon surpass the 0 million TVL threshold), it has also had the effect of placing additional selling pressure on the STRD token and rapidly inflating circulating supply. STRD’s current staked/circulating supply ratio is just over 10%. For security purposes, this ratio should be increased. Ideally, a protocol’s tokenomic model should have the following goals:
 * Bring value to STRD stakers in exchange for locking up tokens as a service to the protocol.
 * Contribute to the success of the protocol by incentivizing and empowering the community.
 * Increase chain security by raising the bonded ratio of tokens.

This proposal aims to accomplish all of these goals by diverting the Stride protocol host chain staking reward commission to STRD stakers.

### Background:
Stride collects 10% of all staking rewards from host chain assets staked through the protocol. Currently, these rewards are accumulating in an on-chain module account. According to Stride’s tokenomics paper, the community will decide the disposition of these rewards. 

### Proposal:
This proposal aims to accomplish the following objectives:
 * Signal to Stride development contributors that the Stride community desires an in-protocol solution to allocate the Stride host-chain staking reward commission fee according to governance-mutable parameters. 
 * Allocate the Stride host chain staking reward commission fee to STRD stakers according to stake weight.

#### Building a Solution to Allocate the Stride Commission Fee
The on-chain parameters necessary to implement this proposal in its entirety do not exist yet, so the proposal will need to be carried out via a subsequent software upgrade. The following is a set of guidelines meant to aid the Stride’s development contributors in building the necessary module flow.

First, the Stride host chain staking reward commission should be capable of being reallocated in a manner that is fully controllable by governance via parameter change proposals. The commission fee should also be capable of being streamed to multiple destination accounts at once (i.e. 10% to account A, 40% to account B, 50% to account C).
So long as the provisions of this proposal are met, the manner of distribution should be left to the discretion of Stride development contributors, who are better suited to understand the development and implementation challenges that go along with distribution.

Swapping the collected rewards to STRD can be accomplished by executing an interchain accounts call from the module responsible for distribution (or some intermediary module) in a manner that:
 * Performs an IBC transfer of the reward asset from Stride > the asset’s native chain > Osmosis; 
 * Swaps the reward asset to STRD on Osmosis;
 * Performs an IBC transfer of the STRD from Osmosis back to Stride chain to be distributed

This can be done in real time as rewards are collected or, if more technically feasible / desirable, at one or more set intervals (epochs) each day.
Second, the rewards that have already been collected should be distributed according to the allocations set forth in this proposal immediately upon implementation of this proposal (or at the first possible epoch following implementation of this proposal if an epoch model is utilized).

#### Allocate the Stride Host Chain Reward Commission to STRD Delegators
To compensate STRD holders for staking their tokens and increase the security of the chain, this proposal seeks to allocate the Stride host chain staking reward commission fee directly to STRD delegators. Using the USD equivalent of the current projected annual rewards of 50,000 and the current bonded ratio, this would provide STRD delegators with an APR of approximately (4.2)%.

### Execution of this Proposal:
Should this proposal pass, Stride development contributors should begin developing the module flow according to the guidelines set forth herein. Once completed and tested, a software upgrade proposal will be put on chain explaining the module flow and the initial commission fee allocations outlined in this proposal.

**The full text of this proposal can be found here:**
https://commonwealth.im/stride/discussion/7652-signaling-proposal-reallocate-the-stride-protocol-commission-fee

detail.title: Stride v3 Aquarius Release
detail.description: **Stride v3 Aquarius Release** This is a proposal to upgrade the chain to v3.0.0 tag (Aquarius Release) of the Stride codebase at block height 1,149,411 which is estimated to occur on Tuesday, November 22nd 2022 at 7pm UTC. Because of the uncertainty in block times, please keep track of the Stride chain for a precise estimate. **Upgrade Features** This upgrade adds the following features: * Airdrop module * Authz support * Automated error handling around closed channels + ICQ **Getting Prepared for the Upgrade** As always, we recommend validators utilize 64GB of RAM. Since state migration is relatively negligible in this upgrade, it is likely possible to get away with less, but still not recommended. If you are unable to have 64GB of RAM, at a minimum have a total of 64GB of swap set to prevent out of memory errors. We highly recommend upgrading with Cosmovisor. To do this, please manually build & copy the strided binary to /cosmovisor/upgrades/v3/bin/. **Details of Upgrade Time** The proposal targets the upgrade proposal block to be 1,149,411, anticipated to be on Tuesday, November 22nd 2022 at 7pm UTC. Because blocks can occur at irregular intervals, please keep an eye on the Stride chain for a precise upgrade time. In case anything concerning happens at upgrade time, we will notify all validators immediately on the #validator-announcements channel on Discord.

detail.title: Stride v2 Orion Release
detail.description:
This is a proposal to upgrade the chain to v2.0.0 tag (“Orion” Release) of the Stride codebase at block height 754,555, which is estimated to occur on Wednsday, October 26th 2022 at 12pm UTC. Because of the uncertainty in block times, please keep track of the Stride chain for a precise estimate.

**Upgrade Features**

This upgrade adds the following features:

- Support for encodings that enable Keplr-Ledger support

- Infra changes that add resilience to ICA failure by relayers

- Additional functionality around rebalancing validators weights

- Ability to add Validators to Host Zones through Governance

**Getting Prepared for the Upgrade**

As always, we recommend validators utilize 64GB of RAM. Since state migration is relatively negligible in this upgrade, it is likely possible to get away with less, but still not recommended. If you are unable to have 64GB of RAM, at a minimum have a total of 64GB of swap set to prevent out of memory errors.

We *highly* recommend upgrading with Cosmovisor. To do this, please manually build & copy the strided binary to /cosmovisor/upgrades/v2/bin/.

**Details of Upgrade Time**

The proposal targets the upgrade proposal block to be 754,555, anticipated to be on Wednesday, October 26th 2022 at 12pm UTC. Because blocks can occur at irregular intervals, please keep an eye on the Stride chain for a precise upgrade time.

In case anything concerning happens at upgrade time, we will notify all validators immediately on the #validator-announcements channel on Discord.
